Looks like it would be easier to not use an Optional here.  Just something like:
final CheckpointAndBlock newFinalizedCheckpoint = tx.getFinalizedCheckpointAndBlock();
...
if (newFinalizedCheckpoint.getEpoch().compareTo(prevFinalizedCheckpoint.getEpoch()) > 0) {
    ... calculate stuff to prune ...
} else {
  .. the empty map stuff ...
}

Although I guess you need the optional to pass into the StoreTransactionUpdates so happy to go either way.

